    "summary": "HERE exposes two documented developer HTTP APIs on this domain scope: the HERE Network Positioning API v2 and the HERE Tracking API; Positioning accepts either HERE app API keys or HERE OAuth bearer tokens, while Tracking requires a HERE Tracking bearer token obtained via its login flow.",
    "description": "HERE provides location technology products and services, including positioning and asset/device tracking capabilities. Its platform documentation covers APIs for location, mapping, routing, IAM, and tracking use cases.",
    "credentials": {
      "here_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "HERE app API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://platform.here.com",
        "setup": "Sign in to the [HERE platform](https://platform.here.com), open [Access Manager](https://platform.here.com/access), select your app, then on **Credentials** → **API Keys** click **Create API key**. The IAM guide for [API keys](https://docs.here.com/identity-and-access-management/docs/plat-using-apikeys) explains that API keys are created per app and are sent as the `apiKey` request parameter.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "here_oauth_token": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "HERE OAuth 2.0 bearer token",
        "generateUrl": "https://platform.here.com",
        "setup": "Create or select an app in [HERE platform Access Manager](https://platform.here.com/access), configure OAuth credentials for that app, then request an access token as described in [How to authorize with OAuth 2.0](https://docs.here.com/identity-and-access-management/docs/how-to-authorize-with-oauth-20) and [Manage API and OAuth access](https://docs.here.com/identity-and-access-management/docs/manage-api-oauth). HERE bearer tokens are app-specific, are sent in the `Authorization: Bearer` header, and by default can last up to 24 hours.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "here_tracking_user_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "HERE Tracking user access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.here.com/tracking/reference/post_users-v2-login",
        "setup": "A user needs active membership in a HERE Tracking project. Then call the Tracking login endpoint as shown in [How to authenticate to the REST API](https://docs.here.com/tracking/docs/getting-started-0-login-user) / [Authentication](https://docs.here.com/tracking/docs/authentication): `POST https://{tcHost}/users/v2/login` with the user's Tracking email, password, and `realm`/organization ID to obtain a bearer token for subsequent Tracking API calls. For platform projects, the docs note the token must then be scoped to the project.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
